139
00:10:58,845 --> 00:11:00,263
Hmm.

140
00:11:09,314 --> 00:11:10,857
Hello. How are you?

141
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:12,609
Hmm.

142
00:11:14,611 --> 00:11:15,779
Won-yeong,

143
00:11:16,571 --> 00:11:18,865
Min-beom was attacked. He's badly hurt.

144
00:11:25,455 --> 00:11:26,456
Let's talk.

145
00:11:33,463 --> 00:11:36,133
Have a reservation?

146
00:11:36,216 --> 00:11:38,510
-We're here to see the owner.
-Okay, just a minute.

147
00:11:38,593 --> 00:11:41,972
-Party of two coming in. Go in, gentlemen.
-Thanks.

148
00:11:42,055 --> 00:11:44,599
Ah! Let's go, bitches!

149
00:11:44,683 --> 00:11:46,810
You're out of your mind.
I'm staying right here.

150
00:11:46,893 --> 00:11:47,728
Oh my! Daddy!

151
00:11:47,811 --> 00:11:49,354
-Hi, Daddy!
-Oh!

152
00:11:49,438 --> 00:11:51,690
Well, look who came
to show his gorgeous face.

153
00:11:51,773 --> 00:11:53,483
Wait, are you wearing
your mother's necklace?

154
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:55,402
You like? It's super pretty.

155
00:11:55,485 --> 00:11:57,279
-Yeah.
-What's up, gorgeous?

156
00:11:57,362 --> 00:11:59,406
Ah, well, I'm looking for someone.

157
00:11:59,489 --> 00:12:00,615
What's your type?

158
00:12:00,699 --> 00:12:01,658
It's a woman.

159
00:12:02,325 --> 00:12:04,661
You've come to the wrong place.

160
00:12:05,537 --> 00:12:07,789
What? Oh no. I'll pass, but thanks anyway.

161
00:12:07,873 --> 00:12:10,292
Because you know
a lot of people around here.

162
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:13,837
How about, if I find her,
can you lower my interest just a smidge?

163
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:14,796
You're crafty.

164
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,757
-Oh, Daddy.
-Yeah, but can you handle it?

165
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,633
Oh, you know I can.

166
00:12:18,717 --> 00:12:21,261
Who's the lucky girl?

167
00:12:25,098 --> 00:12:26,558
Can we have privacy?

168
00:12:27,392 --> 00:12:28,351
Come, come.

169
00:12:29,144 --> 00:12:30,687
-Oh, hey, Gun-woo.
-Yes?

170
00:12:30,771 --> 00:12:32,898
-Don't go anywhere alone.
-Yes.

171
00:12:34,232 --> 00:12:35,609
You know what's strange?

172
00:12:36,109 --> 00:12:37,986
When I said that Min-beom was injured,

173
00:12:38,069 --> 00:12:40,614
you didn't even ask how bad it was.

174
00:12:43,116 --> 00:12:45,368
So why did you sell Min-beom out
to those guys?

175
00:12:47,579 --> 00:12:48,538
He took care of you.

176
00:12:48,622 --> 00:12:53,877
He even set up your university scholarship
with the Iil Group Foundation. Full ride.

177
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:57,672
Min-beom handled every decision.
He handpicked you as his assistant.

178
00:12:58,423 --> 00:13:00,884
He's done everything
for you, Won-yeong. Right?

179
00:13:01,551 --> 00:13:04,054
And you turn on him. For what? More money?

180
00:13:04,554 --> 00:13:05,388
Hey!

181
00:13:06,556 --> 00:13:09,142
Look. He's fucked up right now.

182
00:13:10,936 --> 00:13:12,813
He's unable to even open his eyes.

183
00:13:14,689 --> 00:13:17,150
He took care of you,
and you stab him in the back.

184
00:13:17,234 --> 00:13:18,819
Hey, Cho Won-yeong!

185
00:13:20,862 --> 00:13:22,405
Are you really this much of a lowlife?

186
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:30,080
-Not now!
-Don't speak to him like that! Stop it!

187
00:13:30,163 --> 00:13:32,833
-Get back in your room!
-You didn't do anything wrong!

188
00:13:36,169 --> 00:13:37,170
Look at this.

189
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:40,298
Those bastards did this with a knife.

190
00:13:40,382 --> 00:13:41,299
Enough. Go back now.

191
00:13:41,383 --> 00:13:42,509
Wait.

192
00:13:43,635 --> 00:13:44,678
Tell me what happened.

193
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:48,056
I need the truth now. Yeah?

194
00:13:49,307 --> 00:13:50,433
I'll handle it.

195
00:13:51,142 --> 00:13:51,977
It's okay.

196
00:13:53,937 --> 00:13:54,771
I got it.

197
00:13:55,897 --> 00:13:57,440
Just tell me everything.

198
00:13:58,275 --> 00:14:00,026
So who is she?

199
00:14:02,487 --> 00:14:06,533
Ew. The resolution is terrible,
and her look's so basic.

200
00:14:07,617 --> 00:14:10,120
Hey. Can you try a little harder for me?

201
00:14:10,203 --> 00:14:12,372
No, it's impossible.

202
00:14:12,873 --> 00:14:15,667
Maybe if you lower the interest for me?

203
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:18,670
Give me something good before you start
bargaining with me, idiot.

204
00:14:18,753 --> 00:14:21,923
And give me something to go on.
I have no clues.

205
00:14:22,007 --> 00:14:23,800
Oh yeah!

206
00:14:24,634 --> 00:14:28,221
What's that drug that makes people say
whatever's on their mind?

207
00:14:28,805 --> 00:14:29,764
Oh, Truth Game?

208
00:14:29,848 --> 00:14:31,016
That's the name of it?

209
00:14:31,099 --> 00:14:32,559
Yeah, Truth Game.

210
00:14:33,393 --> 00:14:37,439
This girl gave the waiter something,
and I think it was that drug.

211
00:14:38,356 --> 00:14:42,193
Hmm. Oh my. You'll definitely
have to lower the interest now.

212
00:14:42,277 --> 00:14:45,113
Ah, so there is info
in that head of yours!

213
00:14:46,323 --> 00:14:50,327
I know a guy who imports it
into the country, and distributes it too.

214
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:52,746
Okay. So where's that punk now?

215
00:14:53,413 --> 00:14:57,667
-Uh, will you lower your rate by 5%?
-No way. You're a thief.

216
00:14:57,751 --> 00:14:59,920
-Come on, Daddy, do it one time for me.
-Uh-uh.

217
00:15:00,003 --> 00:15:01,463
-Just one time, for me?
-Let go of me.

218
00:15:01,546 --> 00:15:03,381
-Stop it right now!
-Please? Just this one time.

219
00:15:03,465 --> 00:15:05,008
Fine, 5%. Good enough?

220
00:15:05,091 --> 00:15:06,551
Oh!

221
00:15:06,635 --> 00:15:08,178
-So make the call.
-Yeah.

222
00:15:08,678 --> 00:15:11,473
-Give me a minute, sir.
-He's a good friend, you see.

223
00:15:12,057 --> 00:15:13,099
Yes.

224
00:15:13,183 --> 00:15:14,935
-No, really.
-Yes.

225
00:15:16,311 --> 00:15:21,066
I was on my way home, after
buying some beer at the convenience store.

226
00:15:21,149 --> 00:15:23,944
I was closing the door,
but a hand suddenly came in.

227
00:15:24,027 --> 00:15:25,779
Mm-hmm.

228
00:15:26,655 --> 00:15:28,406
Those bastards kicked me

229
00:15:29,532 --> 00:15:30,867
in the stomach.

230
00:15:30,951 --> 00:15:34,079
And they tied me to a chair.

231
00:15:34,996 --> 00:15:37,165
They said if I screamed…

232
00:15:37,248 --> 00:15:40,251
…they would melt off my face
with hydrochloric acid.

233
00:15:42,212 --> 00:15:43,129
Wow.

234
00:15:43,964 --> 00:15:46,091
-Do you remember what they--
-Uh, Mr. Min?

235
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:49,344
Do you mind if I tell you
the rest of what happened?

236
00:15:49,844 --> 00:15:51,346
Is it okay if my sister leaves?

237
00:15:54,391 --> 00:15:55,475
I appreciate it.

238
00:15:56,184 --> 00:15:57,435
You can go inside.

239
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:07,570
So what happened with your sister's hand?

240
00:16:08,238 --> 00:16:10,198
First, they applied an ointment.

241
00:16:11,408 --> 00:16:13,159
Then they took a knife and cut her.

242
00:16:15,370 --> 00:16:17,372
It was an anesthetic cream.
She didn't feel it.

243
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:20,458
So what did they look like?

244
00:16:21,459 --> 00:16:23,003
There were three of them.

245
00:16:24,879 --> 00:16:29,217
So the largest of the guys
had big eyes with these heavy eyelids.

246
00:16:29,718 --> 00:16:31,052
He was strong.

247
00:16:32,887 --> 00:16:34,848
The second guy did almost all the talking.

248
00:16:35,890 --> 00:16:37,434
His eyebrows were thick.

249
00:16:39,227 --> 00:16:42,522
He was really good
at playing a psychological game.

250
00:16:44,107 --> 00:16:44,941
Go on.

251
00:16:45,734 --> 00:16:48,445
The guy who cut my sister's hand
was very skinny.

252
00:16:50,113 --> 00:16:52,073
He also had a receding hairline.

253
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,452
Something odd with his eyes.

254
00:16:56,911 --> 00:16:58,455
Like he was high or something.

255
00:17:00,915 --> 00:17:04,002
Okay. Did they seem close?

256
00:17:04,627 --> 00:17:06,629
They weren't speaking with each other
very much.

257
00:17:07,213 --> 00:17:09,090
But they worked together like a team.

258
00:17:10,508 --> 00:17:11,342
Good.

259
00:17:13,136 --> 00:17:14,763
They asked me if you

260
00:17:15,513 --> 00:17:16,806
were the president's relative.

261
00:17:18,808 --> 00:17:20,769
It's clear they researched me.

262
00:17:22,687 --> 00:17:24,147
Also, uh…

263
00:17:26,524 --> 00:17:28,193
It's okay. Yeah?

264
00:17:30,987 --> 00:17:32,989
I said something I shouldn't have.

265
00:17:34,699 --> 00:17:36,743
I mentioned where Gun-woo and Woo-jin are.

266
00:17:42,165 --> 00:17:44,084
-Should we alert them now?
-No, no, no.

267
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:46,795
If they move first,

268
00:17:47,712 --> 00:17:49,214
we'll expose Won-yeong.

269
00:17:49,923 --> 00:17:52,300
We need to protect him
for a number of reasons.

270
00:17:52,383 --> 00:17:55,095
I'll have more guards assigned.
This could be helpful.

271
00:17:56,054 --> 00:17:59,224
If they arrive there,
we'll stop those assholes.

272
00:17:59,724 --> 00:18:02,519
The guys in Team 3 are all elite.

273
00:18:03,019 --> 00:18:04,813
I can't go to the police.

274
00:18:05,355 --> 00:18:07,732
-They said they'd kill my family.
-Don't sweat it.

275
00:18:07,816 --> 00:18:09,150
Listen to me.

276
00:18:09,776 --> 00:18:11,861
More undercover cops will be assigned.

277
00:18:12,445 --> 00:18:14,239
For both your sister and this house.

278
00:18:14,739 --> 00:18:17,617
Tell her to act normally.
This is the safest approach.

279
00:18:19,035 --> 00:18:20,203
I'm so sorry.

280
00:18:21,287 --> 00:18:22,872
If they did that to my family,

281
00:18:24,415 --> 00:18:25,917
I'd respond just how you did.

282
00:18:26,751 --> 00:18:28,294
It's not your fault, okay?

283
00:18:28,378 --> 00:18:30,338
They are doing this to your family.

284
00:18:32,507 --> 00:18:33,800
How's my boss?

285
00:18:34,592 --> 00:18:35,677
Will he survive?

286
00:18:36,678 --> 00:18:38,054
So you do care?

287
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:41,099
I'm sorry.

288
00:18:41,182 --> 00:18:42,976
LEE WOO-JEONG
CLASS 39

289
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,853
Pray for him, okay?

290
00:18:46,271 --> 00:18:47,397
Hello, Woo-jeong.

291
00:18:52,610 --> 00:18:53,820
He's here!

292
00:18:55,989 --> 00:18:57,490
Oh.

293
00:18:57,574 --> 00:18:58,575
What's wrong?

294
00:19:01,077 --> 00:19:02,579
You're Kim Gun-woo, right?

295
00:19:03,413 --> 00:19:04,247
Yes.

296
00:19:04,873 --> 00:19:06,958
Holy shit! I'm a big fan.

297
00:19:07,041 --> 00:19:09,627
You and I… met once, remember?

298
00:19:11,713 --> 00:19:13,339
After the Hong Jong-min fight.

299
00:19:13,423 --> 00:19:17,552
After you crushed him. Then you gave me
your autograph, right here!

300
00:19:19,345 --> 00:19:21,097
TO JANG JUN
THANK YOU, KIM GUN-WOO

301
00:19:21,931 --> 00:19:23,975
Oh! Sure. Yes, I remember you.

302
00:19:24,058 --> 00:19:27,353
-Yeah, yeah, yeah. That was a great time!
-Oh sure. Well, hello again.

303
00:19:27,437 --> 00:19:32,025
It's so nice to meet you.
For sure. It's such an honor.

304
00:19:32,525 --> 00:19:33,401
Wow.

305
00:19:34,068 --> 00:19:35,528
Wow, I can't believe this!

306
00:19:35,612 --> 00:19:37,197
Well, I'm thrilled for you.

307
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:40,241
So, um… So how may I help you today?

308
00:19:40,325 --> 00:19:42,619
So Kim Gun-woo is seeking

309
00:19:43,494 --> 00:19:44,454
this woman here.

310
00:19:44,537 --> 00:19:46,247
Do you know her? Have you seen her?

311
00:19:46,331 --> 00:19:50,793
For sure. It's Gi-na. We're super tight.

312
00:19:51,461 --> 00:19:53,630
We have a thing going on.

313
00:19:53,713 --> 00:19:55,548
Did you sell this lady
Truth Game recently?

314
00:19:55,632 --> 00:19:57,383
Yeah. For sure.

315
00:19:57,967 --> 00:19:59,677
Where could she be right now?

316
00:20:01,971 --> 00:20:04,515
Ah, yeah. Have a good evening.

317
00:20:06,017 --> 00:20:07,894
Yes, Mr. Min? It's Moon Gwang-mu.

318
00:20:08,394 --> 00:20:09,437
Any updates?

319
00:20:09,938 --> 00:20:12,607
Yes, I found her! Her name is Gi-na.

320
00:20:13,650 --> 00:20:16,236
I'm heading out to the gambling den now
where she works.

321
00:20:17,654 --> 00:20:19,697
You're serious? You're fantastic.

322
00:20:20,198 --> 00:20:24,535
Well, you believed in me sir, so I really
didn't want to disappoint you, you know.

323
00:20:24,619 --> 00:20:27,872
So let's talk later. Maybe you can help me
with this investigation.

324
00:20:27,956 --> 00:20:29,374
It'd be my honor.

325
00:20:29,457 --> 00:20:32,877
You know, I've actually
always dreamed of being a detective.

326
00:20:34,796 --> 00:20:38,258
Let's meet up to discuss
strategy before making our move together.

327
00:20:38,758 --> 00:20:40,843
Sure, of course. Where should we meet?

328
00:20:41,344 --> 00:20:44,305
Uh, the hotel
where Gun-woo and Woo-jin are staying.

329
00:20:44,389 --> 00:20:48,184
One of my guys has found a lead
off of the picture you sent me.

330
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:50,311
Oh, wow.

331
00:20:51,479 --> 00:20:53,606
Okay, fine, I'll see you soon.
I'm on my way.

332
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:55,108
Great. See you later.

333
00:21:11,249 --> 00:21:14,210
Oh. Perfect timing.

334
00:21:14,294 --> 00:21:17,422
Everyone, this is
my colleague, Lee Woo-jeong.

335
00:21:17,505 --> 00:21:20,091
-Hello.
-New investigator on my team.

336
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:23,636
Hello, everyone. It's a pleasure.

337
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:27,265
Hmm. At school, we were
in the Green Pine Tree Club together.

338
00:21:28,016 --> 00:21:29,434
It's a group founded by seniors.

339
00:21:29,517 --> 00:21:31,936
We are encouraged to stay evergreen
like pine trees,

340
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:34,397
and uphold justice and equality
in our society.

341
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:37,775
It's a secret club which consists
of the best students from each class.

342
00:21:37,859 --> 00:21:38,735
And we met there.

343
00:21:39,235 --> 00:21:42,530
You two haven't met? This is Tae-yeong.
She was in our Cyber Investigation Unit.

344
00:21:42,613 --> 00:21:43,823
It's my pleasure.

345
00:21:49,495 --> 00:21:52,457
I finally get to meet
the Cyber Investigation Unit star.

346
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:54,417
What an honor.

347
00:21:55,293 --> 00:21:58,463
I know very little about boxing,
but I enjoy watching your matches.

348
00:21:58,546 --> 00:22:01,549
I've been a fan since the Rookie
of the Year Tournament during COVID-19.

349
00:22:01,632 --> 00:22:03,217
Uh, that's very kind of you.

350
00:22:03,301 --> 00:22:06,262
-I'm Moon Gwang-mu. It's a real honor.
-Oh, the honor is mine.

351
00:22:06,846 --> 00:22:08,723
I've never met a top student before.

352
00:22:08,806 --> 00:22:10,725
Uh, I'm a top student.

353
00:22:11,851 --> 00:22:14,562
Well, then it's my second time.

354
00:22:18,608 --> 00:22:19,484
Oh.

355
00:22:20,318 --> 00:22:22,070
Can you tell me your name please?

356
00:22:24,864 --> 00:22:26,449
Hong Woo-jin. Yeah.

357
00:22:26,532 --> 00:22:27,784
Aha.

358
00:22:27,867 --> 00:22:30,787
I also competed in that match,
Rookie of the Year tournament.

359
00:22:31,287 --> 00:22:33,206
Oh, forgive me, I didn't… Uh…

360
00:22:33,706 --> 00:22:35,041
Uh…

361
00:22:36,876 --> 00:22:38,211
So, Woo-jeong,

362
00:22:38,711 --> 00:22:41,923
the character "Woo," does it mean "help?"

363
00:22:43,007 --> 00:22:45,301
My character "Woo" means "outstanding."

364
00:22:47,095 --> 00:22:49,972
The "Woo" character, for me,
it means "help," you see.

365
00:22:50,056 --> 00:22:53,935
I propose we get to know each other
so we can help each other out.

366
00:22:54,018 --> 00:22:57,355
Yeah. I'm gonna make sure
to greet you first next time.

367
00:22:57,438 --> 00:23:00,733
Wait. In your name,
does "Woo" mean "help" as well?

368
00:23:01,234 --> 00:23:03,277
-No, it means "friend."
-Ah.

369
00:23:03,361 --> 00:23:07,698
Oh, I think we should make a new club too.
Like you guys.

370
00:23:08,616 --> 00:23:12,036
Three different "Woos" join forces
and fight the enemy,

371
00:23:12,537 --> 00:23:14,580
How about the "Three Woo Club?"

372
00:23:15,998 --> 00:23:18,251
Oh, wow, that's a fantastic idea.

373
00:23:18,334 --> 00:23:20,795
Great, great,
I hope your new club lasts forever,

374
00:23:20,878 --> 00:23:22,839
but I think it's time to get to work now.

375
00:23:22,922 --> 00:23:24,382
-Yes, of course.
-Great.

376
00:23:27,802 --> 00:23:29,262
OCTO ROMA NATURALIA CASE FILE

377
00:23:29,345 --> 00:23:31,639
Let's begin with the investigation report.

378
00:23:35,226 --> 00:23:38,604
The watch in the photo you sent us
is a limited edition model.

379
00:23:38,688 --> 00:23:41,482
In Korea, it's been purchased
by only two people.

380
00:23:41,566 --> 00:23:44,193
One, a pro soccer player
who currently plays in Europe,

381
00:23:44,277 --> 00:23:45,486
and the other,

382
00:23:46,112 --> 00:23:48,197
former Special Forces Officer
Yun Tae-Geom.

383
00:23:48,281 --> 00:23:49,240
Wait. That's the guy.

384
00:23:50,908 --> 00:23:53,453
-Him? You sure?
-Oh yeah. He fought us.

385
00:23:55,621 --> 00:23:58,458
Yun Tae-geom. He was born in 1990.

386
00:23:58,541 --> 00:24:01,919
In 2009, he enlisted as an NCO
in Army Special Warfare Command.

387
00:24:02,003 --> 00:24:04,922
He served with
the 17th Airborne Special Forces.

388
00:24:05,006 --> 00:24:06,799
And his specialty? Explosives.

389
00:24:06,883 --> 00:24:09,010
According to fellow soldiers,
he was highly intelligent,

390
00:24:09,093 --> 00:24:11,971
and excelled at making
improvised explosive devices.

391
00:24:12,054 --> 00:24:14,682
He was dishonorably discharged
in April 2020.

392
00:24:14,765 --> 00:24:16,893
The reason for that is classified.
I'm looking into it.

393
00:24:18,019 --> 00:24:20,021
I researched his family
and personal history.

394
00:24:20,104 --> 00:24:21,898
SPOUSE: HAN EUN-JI, DECEASED
CHILD: YUN MIN-A

395
00:24:21,981 --> 00:24:23,441
He has a young daughter.

396
00:24:24,525 --> 00:24:27,361
-And where is she?
-Lives with her grandmother in Daejeon.

397
00:24:27,445 --> 00:24:29,489
I still haven't figured out
his wife's death.

398
00:24:29,572 --> 00:24:31,073
Where's our former officer now?

399
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:35,536
He went to Thailand in March last year
and hasn't come back officially.

400
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:39,123
I think he's here.
With forged identification and a visa.

401
00:24:40,082 --> 00:24:42,668
Okay, everyone, gather around.

402
00:24:42,752 --> 00:24:43,711
Of course.

403
00:24:51,594 --> 00:24:52,762
This is the head.

404
00:24:53,513 --> 00:24:54,764
This is Yun Tae-geom.

405
00:24:55,765 --> 00:24:58,434
Our special forces guy. He's the fixer,
the muscle. You follow me?

406
00:24:58,518 --> 00:24:59,852
Kang In-beom.

407
00:25:00,353 --> 00:25:03,773
Not sure yet
what this bastard's role is in all this.

408
00:25:04,398 --> 00:25:05,775
But according to Mr. Cho…

409
00:25:05,858 --> 00:25:06,984
The voice?

410
00:25:07,068 --> 00:25:08,861
Exactly. That's what I'm thinking.

411
00:25:08,945 --> 00:25:11,239
First, we should go over
what we know for sure.

412
00:25:11,906 --> 00:25:13,533
This here is the junkie doctor.

413
00:25:13,616 --> 00:25:17,036
Maybe this asshole is responsible
for that drug on Min-beom.

414
00:25:17,662 --> 00:25:20,289
The one with the thick eyebrows
works logistics.

415
00:25:20,373 --> 00:25:23,209
Like gathering intel, sizing things up,
and bringing in the hired guys.

416
00:25:23,292 --> 00:25:25,920
He probably handled everything
for Kang In-beom's escape from prison,

417
00:25:26,003 --> 00:25:27,880
making sure everyone had
everything they need.

418
00:25:27,964 --> 00:25:29,340
Don't forget their computer expert.

419
00:25:29,423 --> 00:25:31,259
-So he's number six, right?
-Okay.

420
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:36,514
Wow, that's a pretty big crew.
Just their monthly salaries are a fortune.

421
00:25:36,597 --> 00:25:40,518
Um, sir, there's something
I wanted to share with you directly.

422
00:25:41,018 --> 00:25:43,104
When were at Golden Slumber before,

423
00:25:44,730 --> 00:25:45,856
I got a call.

424
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:49,610
-On your phone?
-Yes.

425
00:25:50,111 --> 00:25:52,446
-What did he say?
-He directly threatened him.

426
00:25:53,114 --> 00:25:56,075
If he didn't take part in their league,
everyone around him is in danger.

427
00:25:56,158 --> 00:25:57,910
Did you get his number, by chance?

428
00:25:57,994 --> 00:25:59,662
I guess not.

429
00:26:00,746 --> 00:26:03,416
-He say anything else to you?
-Gun-woo.

430
00:26:06,335 --> 00:26:08,212
The detective who died
right in front of us.

431
00:26:09,714 --> 00:26:11,716
One of his fellow officers sold him out.

432
00:26:12,216 --> 00:26:14,176
He was paid off
with a massive amount of cash.

433
00:26:17,638 --> 00:26:19,348
Wow.

434
00:26:22,893 --> 00:26:25,938
For right now, I want only the people here
to work on this.

435
00:26:26,814 --> 00:26:28,441
-Yeah.
-Okay.

436
00:26:29,358 --> 00:26:31,110
Now, in a way,

437
00:26:32,445 --> 00:26:35,072
this is a way more intelligent,
better-run organization

438
00:26:35,156 --> 00:26:36,824
than when we fought Kim Myeong-gil.

439
00:26:36,907 --> 00:26:39,410
No need to be worried. Justice is with us.

440
00:26:40,870 --> 00:26:44,707
There are quite a few things we need
to do, and they all must be done at once.

441
00:26:44,790 --> 00:26:48,377
Mr. Moon and Gun-woo, find that woman now.

442
00:26:48,461 --> 00:26:49,754
-Okay.
-Yes.

443
00:26:49,837 --> 00:26:53,466
Woo-jeong, check the footage and see where
the guy who stabbed Detective Choi went.

444
00:26:53,549 --> 00:26:54,425
Okay.

445
00:26:54,508 --> 00:26:56,927
Woo-jin, come with me
to meet Yun Tae-geom's mother.

446
00:26:57,011 --> 00:26:57,887
Got it.

447
00:26:57,970 --> 00:26:59,847
Okay. I want you watching the website.

448
00:27:00,681 --> 00:27:03,225
If you learn anything about this asshole,
contact me right away.

449
00:27:03,309 --> 00:27:05,019
This lowlife got money to the police.

450
00:27:05,102 --> 00:27:08,230
I don't know what he did before,
but he's got connections everywhere.

451
00:27:08,731 --> 00:27:11,192
I think… I think he was likely police.

452
00:27:11,776 --> 00:27:12,610
Yes.

453
00:27:12,693 --> 00:27:15,988
And we all must be safe. Bring it in.

454
00:27:16,072 --> 00:27:17,239
Yeah.

455
00:27:20,785 --> 00:27:22,870
-One, two, three.
-Let's go!

456
00:27:52,858 --> 00:27:55,778
Which camera shows the best view
of where he goes next?

457
00:27:55,861 --> 00:27:57,279
-Give me a second.
-Okay.

458
00:27:57,780 --> 00:27:59,448
This one should be the best angle.

459
00:28:23,139 --> 00:28:27,351
I'll give you a sedative.

460
00:28:27,435 --> 00:28:30,479
-It'll definitely help ease your pain.
-No!

461
00:28:31,063 --> 00:28:32,273
I can do this.

462
00:28:32,773 --> 00:28:34,191
I can do this on my own.

463
00:28:34,275 --> 00:28:36,861
It's very possible
that you'll need a liver transplant.

464
00:28:36,944 --> 00:28:37,987
The sedative will help.

465
00:28:38,070 --> 00:28:39,280
I said I can do this on my own!

466
00:28:39,363 --> 00:28:41,323
Keep this up, you'll be in serious danger.

467
00:28:41,407 --> 00:28:43,993
I can do this. I can do this!

468
00:29:18,194 --> 00:29:19,028
Hey.

469
00:29:19,528 --> 00:29:20,821
-Hmm?
-What are you doing?

470
00:29:22,490 --> 00:29:24,992
Woo-jin. You know how much this costs?

471
00:29:25,951 --> 00:29:28,120
Not really sure. Thirty thousand?

472
00:29:30,164 --> 00:29:31,457
Are you serious?

473
00:29:32,208 --> 00:29:33,959
So, how much is it?

474
00:29:34,043 --> 00:29:35,711
This costs about ten times that.

475
00:29:36,212 --> 00:29:37,338
Huh?

476
00:29:37,838 --> 00:29:40,549
It's a limited edition.
There's a waiting list for it.

477
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:42,301
Oh.

478
00:29:44,678 --> 00:29:45,554
Wait.

479
00:29:46,138 --> 00:29:47,306
Hmm?

480
00:29:47,389 --> 00:29:50,017
Now I know
why you wanted me here with you.

481
00:29:51,936 --> 00:29:54,939
-Why?
-To see Yun Tae-geom's mother.

482
00:29:55,022 --> 00:29:56,190
And then butter her up.

483
00:29:56,690 --> 00:29:59,485
Then we can meet
Yun Tae-geom in person, right?

484
00:30:00,069 --> 00:30:02,863
I'll try. I'll do my best.

485
00:30:05,282 --> 00:30:08,994
Okay. You're overestimating
yourself here, Woo-jin.

486
00:30:11,121 --> 00:30:13,666
You handle the little kid.

487
00:30:14,208 --> 00:30:16,794
I'll handle the mother.

488
00:30:19,421 --> 00:30:21,298
-Uh, of course.
-Good.

489
00:30:25,594 --> 00:30:27,012
Who is it?

490
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:29,223
-Oh yes, hello there.
-Yes?

491
00:30:29,306 --> 00:30:32,601
Would you mind
if I… speak to you for a few minutes?

492
00:30:33,936 --> 00:30:34,770
Oh.

493
00:30:36,021 --> 00:30:36,939
Okay.

494
00:30:39,024 --> 00:30:40,776
He left us two years ago.

495
00:30:41,485 --> 00:30:44,071
He said he got some job in Thailand.

496
00:30:45,114 --> 00:30:47,241
And he was going to guard
this rich person.

497
00:30:48,033 --> 00:30:49,577
He hasn't been back since.

498
00:30:50,202 --> 00:30:51,620
Does he return for holidays?

499
00:30:52,788 --> 00:30:53,873
No.

500
00:30:54,456 --> 00:30:55,457
Oh.

501
00:30:56,041 --> 00:30:58,252
Min-a must miss her dad so much.

502
00:31:00,713 --> 00:31:02,506
Do you both keep in touch?

503
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:06,260
No.

504
00:31:06,343 --> 00:31:08,095
Hmm. Wow.

505
00:31:08,596 --> 00:31:10,180
He must miss her a lot.

506
00:31:10,681 --> 00:31:13,225
I couldn't do that.
I have a young daughter like Min-a too.

507
00:31:13,309 --> 00:31:14,602
Yes.

508
00:31:15,102 --> 00:31:17,271
I don't know what that boy is thinking.

509
00:31:18,898 --> 00:31:20,858
I… I don't wanna know.

510
00:31:29,491 --> 00:31:30,367
Mm.

511
00:31:31,076 --> 00:31:32,578
That's a great drawing.

512
00:31:33,621 --> 00:31:37,458
I see that uncle's stuffing his face
with all of Min-a's snacks.

513
00:31:43,297 --> 00:31:44,548
Uh… Uh…

514
00:31:47,509 --> 00:31:50,679
Min-a, listen. How about
we do something else?

515
00:31:51,347 --> 00:31:52,222
What else do you like?

516
00:31:53,057 --> 00:31:55,976
Do you like stickers?
There's plenty of stickers in my room.

517
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:58,395
Oh yeah! Let's go!

518
00:31:59,271 --> 00:32:01,565
She's so pretty.

519
00:32:06,946 --> 00:32:09,031
Tell me. Why'd he leave the military?

520
00:32:09,865 --> 00:32:11,825
Mina's mom. The hospital.

521
00:32:13,118 --> 00:32:14,954
Those costs weren't covered
by military income.

522
00:32:16,622 --> 00:32:17,665
She was sick?

523
00:32:18,457 --> 00:32:19,291
Mm.

524
00:32:21,085 --> 00:32:22,419
She had cancer.

525
00:32:23,212 --> 00:32:24,755
Pancreatic. It was bad.

526
00:32:25,381 --> 00:32:26,548
Oh.

527
00:32:28,759 --> 00:32:30,219
That's really hard.

528
00:32:31,637 --> 00:32:32,972
Wow, Min-a.

529
00:32:34,014 --> 00:32:37,935
This is a lot of stickers you're using.
Are you positive it's not too many?

530
00:32:38,852 --> 00:32:39,687
Yeah.

531
00:32:40,270 --> 00:32:44,900
I bet you also like to stick these on your
dad too. I'm sure he enjoys that, right?

532
00:32:44,984 --> 00:32:47,277
Last time, I stuck a hundred on his face.

533
00:32:47,361 --> 00:32:48,779
When was that?

534
00:32:49,571 --> 00:32:50,948
This past Monday.

535
00:32:52,533 --> 00:32:53,492
Oh.

536
00:32:54,952 --> 00:32:56,161
This past Monday.

537
00:33:00,666 --> 00:33:03,877
Oh, then I bet your dad
bought you that scooter three nights ago.

538
00:33:03,961 --> 00:33:06,755
So it's this past Monday night.
Is that right?

539
00:33:07,339 --> 00:33:08,173
Yeah.

540
00:33:08,257 --> 00:33:10,968
Oh. Having fun with it? Is it cool?

541
00:33:11,635 --> 00:33:14,013
Well, I'm a little scared of it.

542
00:33:20,394 --> 00:33:23,647
How about… if I gave you a private lesson?

543
00:33:23,731 --> 00:33:25,149
Yeah!

544
00:33:25,232 --> 00:33:26,817
Oh yeah!

545
00:33:27,735 --> 00:33:29,069
Here we go.

546
00:33:30,154 --> 00:33:34,074
Hi, Grandma! I'm gonna ride my scooter
with my new friend.

547
00:33:34,158 --> 00:33:37,244
I'll make sure
she rides safely and carefully.

548
00:33:37,327 --> 00:33:39,955
-See you later, Grandma!
-Be safe.

549
00:33:40,039 --> 00:33:40,873
Sure.

550
00:33:44,793 --> 00:33:45,919
Here we go!

551
00:33:49,256 --> 00:33:50,257
So, ma'am…

552
00:33:52,426 --> 00:33:54,303
actually, we know about your son.

553
00:33:56,472 --> 00:33:58,265
Ah, okay, uh… Well…

554
00:33:58,348 --> 00:34:03,020
If you can help me out today,
I can help your son safely return home.

555
00:34:04,438 --> 00:34:05,564
I promise that.

556
00:34:12,654 --> 00:34:14,239
Uh, okay, okay…

557
00:34:14,323 --> 00:34:17,743
So how am I, uh, supposed to help?

558
00:34:18,243 --> 00:34:22,414
It's simple. You just have to call me
when he calls you.

559
00:34:25,918 --> 00:34:28,337
-Okay, show me what's next.
-Sure.

560
00:34:32,966 --> 00:34:34,259
Now zoom in on this camera angle.

561
00:34:55,072 --> 00:34:56,990
-Okay, pause it there, please.
-Yes.

562
00:35:02,538 --> 00:35:06,458
-Ah. Excuse me. Give me a minute.
-Take your time.

563
00:35:07,918 --> 00:35:08,961
Hi, Woo-jeong.

564
00:35:11,672 --> 00:35:12,548
What's up?

565
00:35:12,631 --> 00:35:15,551
I reviewed the CCTV footage
and found the fourth suspect.

566
00:35:15,634 --> 00:35:16,552
Oh yeah?

567
00:35:16,635 --> 00:35:19,847
-Can you text me that picture?
-Yeah, I'll send it now.

568
00:35:20,722 --> 00:35:23,267
And we just talked
to Yun Tae-geom's mother

569
00:35:23,350 --> 00:35:26,311
and we learned that his wife
had pancreatic cancer.

570
00:35:26,395 --> 00:35:29,731
It seems he borrowed cash from loan sharks
for her treatment.

571
00:35:29,815 --> 00:35:32,901
When he couldn't pay the interest,
the sharks caused trouble at his base,

572
00:35:32,985 --> 00:35:33,902
so he was discharged.

573
00:35:34,486 --> 00:35:35,821
Must have been tough.

574
00:35:35,904 --> 00:35:38,740
Yeah, right?
I feel for the guy a little bit.

575
00:35:40,075 --> 00:35:42,369
Give me his number
and I'll see if I'm able to track it.

576
00:35:42,452 --> 00:35:45,038
I think he's using a burner phone.
She says his number changes.

577
00:35:45,122 --> 00:35:46,415
What should we do?

578
00:35:47,082 --> 00:35:49,459
Well, yeah, we could notify the police,

579
00:35:50,460 --> 00:35:53,255
but in all likelihood
there are cops out there

580
00:35:53,755 --> 00:35:55,007
who were bribed by them too.

581
00:35:55,674 --> 00:35:58,427
If we put out a wanted notice,
Yun Tae-geom will disappear.

582
00:35:58,510 --> 00:35:59,344
Ah.

583
00:35:59,428 --> 00:36:02,472
Why don't we leave Yun Tae-geom
and Mr. Cho alone for now.

584
00:36:03,098 --> 00:36:04,683
So we can stay under the radar.

585
00:36:06,101 --> 00:36:07,853
And Yun Tae-geom and I must meet.

586
00:36:08,353 --> 00:36:11,440
He's clearly a tough guy,
but he does this for his family.

587
00:36:11,940 --> 00:36:14,651
It's possible we could
bring him to our side.

588
00:36:14,735 --> 00:36:15,944
Yes, that works for me.

589
00:36:16,028 --> 00:36:18,405
So for now,
send me that bastard's picture.

590
00:36:19,031 --> 00:36:19,865
Sure.

591
00:36:20,908 --> 00:36:23,327
Okay, it's time to see his face.

592
00:36:24,786 --> 00:36:25,621
HONG MIN-BEOM

593
00:36:26,246 --> 00:36:27,581
Oh!

594
00:36:29,750 --> 00:36:32,711
-Hello, sir! How are you?
-Where are you?

595
00:36:34,963 --> 00:36:38,217
Investigating in Daejeon. I'm with Woo-jin
right now. How are you feeling?

596
00:36:39,551 --> 00:36:40,802
It's painful.

597
00:36:42,554 --> 00:36:44,014
But it's getting better.

598
00:36:44,097 --> 00:36:47,100
That's so good to hear.

599
00:36:47,935 --> 00:36:49,728
You know everyone was worried.

600
00:36:53,065 --> 00:36:54,775
Just a few more days.

601
00:36:57,236 --> 00:36:58,528
Then I'm back.

602
00:36:58,612 --> 00:37:00,405
Yes, of course. Take your time.

603
00:37:00,489 --> 00:37:01,990
We'll talk soon.

604
00:37:02,074 --> 00:37:03,408
Yes, yes, for sure.

605
00:37:07,871 --> 00:37:10,374
Oh wait, here it is.

606
00:37:22,344 --> 00:37:25,264
Hmm. So this is what it's like
to be a detective.

607
00:37:25,764 --> 00:37:27,099
Uh, yeah, sort of.

608
00:37:29,017 --> 00:37:30,352
-Uh, Jun.
-Yeah?

609
00:37:30,852 --> 00:37:33,563
Be honest. Is she gonna be here?

610
00:37:33,647 --> 00:37:36,233
She goes to work right around this time.

611
00:37:36,316 --> 00:37:38,527
This is where I dropped her off once.

612
00:37:38,610 --> 00:37:39,736
Oh, look!

613
00:37:51,039 --> 00:37:54,126
Is that her? Yeah, that's her for sure.

614
00:38:00,048 --> 00:38:03,927
Okay. Okay, so you take the elevator
to the seventh floor.

615
00:38:04,011 --> 00:38:05,429
When you get out, you take a left.

616
00:38:06,013 --> 00:38:08,932
Then walk down that long hallway.
Finally, you'll come to a door.

617
00:38:09,016 --> 00:38:11,351
-You'll see a bunch of playing cards--
-What happens there?

618
00:38:11,435 --> 00:38:14,229
Uh, high stakes games
of blackjack, poker, mah-jongg.

619
00:38:14,855 --> 00:38:17,482
A lot of the regular players
are criminals,

620
00:38:17,566 --> 00:38:19,234
so many of them are armed.

621
00:38:19,318 --> 00:38:21,278
Guns, knives, and even axes.

622
00:38:21,778 --> 00:38:23,905
You have to be extremely careful.

623
00:38:24,698 --> 00:38:26,783
Yes. Thank you for your advice.

624
00:38:29,494 --> 00:38:30,537
Let's do this!

625
00:38:30,620 --> 00:38:31,997
Or whatever you say.

626
00:38:33,081 --> 00:38:34,041
Let's do this.

627
00:38:53,060 --> 00:38:55,062
-Ah.
-Mr. Min, we found the girl.

628
00:38:55,145 --> 00:38:56,730
-Her name's Gi-na.
-Great.

629
00:38:56,813 --> 00:38:58,732
She works here, on the seventh floor.

630
00:38:58,815 --> 00:39:00,484
-Great work, you guys.
-Thanks.

631
00:39:09,659 --> 00:39:12,996
Oh right. I had a case once
in this building.

632
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:15,040
There was a serial killer
hiding here years ago.

633
00:39:16,041 --> 00:39:18,335
So this building was built
back in the '70s.

634
00:39:18,418 --> 00:39:20,545
Things were different then.
See the fire escape?

635
00:39:21,380 --> 00:39:25,258
Oh. So my guess,
she'll either use that stairway,

636
00:39:25,342 --> 00:39:28,220
or take the elevator
directly to the parking lot underground.

637
00:39:28,303 --> 00:39:30,514
So here's the plan.
Two of us flush her out.

638
00:39:30,597 --> 00:39:33,975
One of us watches the fire escape,
and the other covers the garage.

639
00:39:34,851 --> 00:39:35,685
Uh, sir?

640
00:39:36,728 --> 00:39:39,231
Can I join Mr. Moon
going in the main entrance?

641
00:39:39,314 --> 00:39:40,315
Mm.

642
00:39:41,066 --> 00:39:42,859
-You sure?
-Yes.

643
00:39:44,611 --> 00:39:46,822
Then, sir, I'll take the fire escape.

644
00:39:47,906 --> 00:39:50,992
Okay. Everyone, be careful.
Let's, not get hurt.

645
00:39:51,076 --> 00:39:52,994
Okay, guys, bring it in.

646
00:39:53,578 --> 00:39:55,122
-One, two, three…
-Let's do it!

647
00:39:55,205 --> 00:39:56,039
Yeah.

648
00:40:22,149 --> 00:40:23,191
You have gloves?

649
00:40:28,655 --> 00:40:30,449
Ah, shit.

650
00:40:41,001 --> 00:40:43,295
-Yeah?
-I'm President Moon from Dream On Capital.

651
00:40:43,378 --> 00:40:44,212
I'd like to play.

652
00:40:46,339 --> 00:40:48,758
This fucking guy.

653
00:40:50,427 --> 00:40:51,261
What?

654
00:40:51,344 --> 00:40:55,390
Jang Jun mentioned this joint. He said
it's a great place for some gambling.

655
00:40:57,476 --> 00:40:58,810
This is getting on my nerves.

656
00:41:21,291 --> 00:41:22,334
Over here.

657
00:41:26,713 --> 00:41:28,632
Okay.

658
00:41:32,761 --> 00:41:35,013
-I would like more chips, please.
-Hmm?

659
00:41:36,014 --> 00:41:38,225
You keep dealing me the same crappy hand.

660
00:41:38,308 --> 00:41:39,935
First time playing mah-jongg.

661
00:41:40,018 --> 00:41:41,102
Oh, come on!

662
00:41:41,186 --> 00:41:43,647
You're on a cold streak.
I've never seen it this bad.

663
00:41:43,730 --> 00:41:45,065
Last bets, gentlemen.

664
00:41:47,609 --> 00:41:49,528
-These guys are cops!
-Wait, who?

665
00:41:49,611 --> 00:41:51,613
Cops. Let's move!

666
00:41:53,823 --> 00:41:56,243
Hey, Gun-woo, stop her!
She's getting away!

667
00:41:56,993 --> 00:41:57,869
Bastard!

668
00:42:33,697 --> 00:42:34,698
Gun-woo!

669
00:43:03,435 --> 00:43:04,269
Huh?

670
00:43:20,243 --> 00:43:21,244
Shit!

671
00:43:23,496 --> 00:43:24,748
Hey!

672
00:43:38,511 --> 00:43:39,929
Let go of me, asshole!

673
00:43:53,151 --> 00:43:55,195
-Come here, fucker. I got you.
-Wait a minute!

674
00:43:55,278 --> 00:43:58,948
Wait. Listen, I'm not a cop.
I'm not! I'm a small business owner!

675
00:43:59,032 --> 00:44:00,992
You think we give a shit?

676
00:44:36,277 --> 00:44:39,739
[indistinct yelling in distance]

677
00:44:39,823 --> 00:44:41,282
I will kill you!

678
00:44:42,117 --> 00:44:43,326
Gwang-mu!

679
00:44:43,410 --> 00:44:44,285
Hey!

680
00:44:45,829 --> 00:44:47,330
-What? No!
-Sir! Sir!

681
00:44:47,414 --> 00:44:49,541
-No, stop it! No, no, wait!
-It's me. It's me.

682
00:44:49,624 --> 00:44:51,459
-You okay?
-Yeah. I'm fine.

683
00:44:51,543 --> 00:44:52,919
Are you sure you're okay?

684
00:44:53,002 --> 00:44:56,256
Oh yeah. As long as I'm with you,
I'll live, okay?

685
00:44:56,339 --> 00:44:57,507
She must be close. Let's go.

686
00:44:57,590 --> 00:44:59,050
-Right.
-Okay.

687
00:44:59,134 --> 00:45:00,135
Shit.

688
00:45:04,931 --> 00:45:06,683
Ah, shit.

689
00:45:06,766 --> 00:45:08,476
-You coming?
-You go ahead.

690
00:45:25,243 --> 00:45:26,828
Let's go quietly.

691
00:45:27,328 --> 00:45:28,329
[Gi-na sighs]

692
00:45:31,416 --> 00:45:32,417
[knife slices]

693
00:45:34,043 --> 00:45:36,212
Put the knife down. Let's go.

694
00:45:36,963 --> 00:45:38,882
Ah, shit.

695
00:45:39,924 --> 00:45:42,510
Someone help! He's attacking--

696
00:45:46,055 --> 00:45:46,973
[music fades]

697
00:45:47,557 --> 00:45:49,350
-[sighs]
-[cell phone buzzing]

698
00:45:49,434 --> 00:45:50,310
Yes, hello?

699
00:45:50,393 --> 00:45:52,061
-Tae-yeong, hey.
-Yes?

700
00:45:52,145 --> 00:45:54,063
I took her phone from her. What's next?

701
00:45:54,147 --> 00:45:55,315
What's the model?

702
00:45:55,815 --> 00:45:58,693
It's an iPhone 14 or 15. Not sure.

703
00:45:58,777 --> 00:46:01,696
iPhone cameras can be opened
without a password.

704
00:46:01,780 --> 00:46:03,990
I'm going to send you a message
with a QR code.

705
00:46:04,073 --> 00:46:05,450
Use her phone to scan it.

706
00:46:05,533 --> 00:46:06,868
Okay.

707
00:46:06,951 --> 00:46:08,953
[tense music playing]

708
00:46:14,542 --> 00:46:15,919
Got it. Hang on a minute.

709
00:46:26,471 --> 00:46:27,305
GI-NA

710
00:46:27,388 --> 00:46:28,723
MONEY

711
00:46:33,311 --> 00:46:34,187
[sighs]

712
00:46:34,979 --> 00:46:36,397
HOW MUCH

713
00:46:36,481 --> 00:46:37,649
HOW MUCH?
MANJI

714
00:46:37,732 --> 00:46:38,983
GROUP CHAT? WHY NOT DM ME?

715
00:46:39,067 --> 00:46:39,943
Whoa!

716
00:46:40,819 --> 00:46:41,778
IS THE JOB JUICY?

717
00:46:41,861 --> 00:46:42,987
YOUR PRICE PLUS BONUS

718
00:46:43,071 --> 00:46:43,905
LEAVING IT TO YOU

719
00:46:43,988 --> 00:46:44,948
JUST SPIKE A DRINK

720
00:46:45,031 --> 00:46:45,907
USE MY OWN DRUG?

721
00:46:45,990 --> 00:46:47,575
-LET'S TALK IN PERSON.
-WHERE?

722
00:46:47,659 --> 00:46:49,077
I'LL CALL YOU. MEET ME THERE

723
00:46:49,160 --> 00:46:49,994
OKAY

724
00:46:50,870 --> 00:46:52,330
Oh, shit.

725
00:46:53,748 --> 00:46:54,833
I found this, sir.

726
00:46:54,916 --> 00:46:55,750
Yeah?

727
00:46:55,834 --> 00:46:58,127
She's the one
who spiked President Hong's drink.

728
00:46:58,211 --> 00:47:00,672
She met with the guy
who arranged the job today.

729
00:47:00,755 --> 00:47:01,923
Where?

730
00:47:02,006 --> 00:47:04,926
The Entra Hotel.
There's a bar on the second floor.

731
00:47:05,009 --> 00:47:06,469
At 11:00 this morning.

732
00:47:08,096 --> 00:47:12,725
Tae-yeong, call the hotel
and see if Yun Tae-geom is booked there.

733
00:47:12,809 --> 00:47:14,602
Yes, sir.

734
00:47:15,228 --> 00:47:17,146
Good evening, Entra Hotel lobby.

735
00:47:17,730 --> 00:47:20,525
This is Kang Tae-yeong,
Cyber Unit, Seoul Metro Police.

736
00:47:20,608 --> 00:47:23,027
Can you provide the room number
for Yun Tae-geom, please?

737
00:47:26,030 --> 00:47:28,116
So be aware that if you do not cooperate,

738
00:47:28,199 --> 00:47:30,660
you may be charged
with obstruction of justice.

739
00:47:32,954 --> 00:47:35,164
He's staying in the penthouse
as a long-term guest.

740
00:47:36,291 --> 00:47:37,709
Thanks for your cooperation.

741
00:47:38,585 --> 00:47:40,712
HE'S A LONG-TERM GUEST IN THE PENTHOUSE

742
00:47:41,504 --> 00:47:43,298
-It's him. We got him.
-Oh!

743
00:47:43,381 --> 00:47:46,885
Now take this young lady
and go somewhere safe.

744
00:47:46,968 --> 00:47:49,345
-Yes, of course.
-I'll stick with Mr. Moon right now

745
00:47:49,429 --> 00:47:50,805
-Sure.
-I'll stay with you, sir.

746
00:47:50,889 --> 00:47:51,806
Let's go.

747
00:47:51,890 --> 00:47:52,891
[music fades]

748
00:47:57,729 --> 00:47:59,731
[tense music playing]

749
00:48:01,065 --> 00:48:03,943
[telephone ringing]

750
00:48:04,527 --> 00:48:09,032
You were right. Bringing a mainstream
fighter into IKFC was a huge success.

751
00:48:09,115 --> 00:48:11,576
So you see the profit.

752
00:48:11,659 --> 00:48:14,495
We made more money
than we have ever made previously.

753
00:48:14,579 --> 00:48:17,290
I told you
it was gonna be immensely helpful.

754
00:48:21,753 --> 00:48:25,465
Okay. So now, we will bring in another
mainstream fighter. His name is Gun-woo.

755
00:48:25,548 --> 00:48:29,135
He just destroyed Adik and is the current
super-middleweight champion of the world,

756
00:48:29,218 --> 00:48:32,513
and we convinced him to join our IKFC37.

757
00:48:32,597 --> 00:48:34,807
Our numbers will be bigger than ever.

758
00:48:36,059 --> 00:48:36,976
Hey.

759
00:48:37,602 --> 00:48:40,563
He's an infighter.
There will be a lot of blood.

760
00:48:42,315 --> 00:48:43,399
They're gonna love it.

761
00:48:44,776 --> 00:48:48,738
And we will market Gun-woo
to Korea, Japan, Taiwan, Thailand.

762
00:48:48,821 --> 00:48:51,449
All our Asian markets.
The bets will be higher than ever.

763
00:48:51,532 --> 00:48:55,119
All because he's an Asian fighter
who they can cheer for.

764
00:48:56,162 --> 00:48:58,748
Look, gentlemen. Like I mentioned before,

765
00:48:58,831 --> 00:49:02,210
I'm still divided between your IKFC…

766
00:49:03,169 --> 00:49:06,756
Let's be honest, needs a major overhaul.

767
00:49:07,256 --> 00:49:13,096
…and an established moneymaking
Dutch soccer gambling site empire,

768
00:49:13,179 --> 00:49:15,014
called Hatricks.

769
00:49:17,558 --> 00:49:18,476
But…

770
00:49:19,227 --> 00:49:20,311
[sighs]

771
00:49:22,939 --> 00:49:26,526
…if you continue to make steady profits,

772
00:49:27,026 --> 00:49:32,323
I guess I can pour in
up to 400 million dollars

773
00:49:32,407 --> 00:49:38,204
for 51% of the shares
of your little up-and-coming startup.

774
00:49:38,705 --> 00:49:39,539
Sound good?

775
00:49:41,457 --> 00:49:43,710
Okay, we will continue
to make arrangements.

776
00:49:44,460 --> 00:49:46,587
Great. Ciao.

777
00:49:50,091 --> 00:49:52,552
Hold on. You said he'd buy it.

778
00:49:53,553 --> 00:49:55,847
Did that fucking sound
like he was interested?

779
00:49:57,932 --> 00:50:01,310
Oh, he's only bluffing.
As long as we land Gun-woo, we'll be fine.

780
00:50:02,103 --> 00:50:03,771
You better be right, you motherfucker.

781
00:50:03,855 --> 00:50:08,943
[telephone ringing]

782
00:50:16,492 --> 00:50:18,578
-What?
-This is the front desk.

783
00:50:18,661 --> 00:50:22,540
Man-bae mentioned that I should call
if anything suspicious happened.

784
00:50:23,041 --> 00:50:25,209
Well, the police
just called the front desk.

785
00:50:27,879 --> 00:50:28,880
[phone clatters]

786
00:50:29,797 --> 00:50:31,924
-[dramatic music playing]
-[sirens wailing]

787
00:51:00,787 --> 00:51:02,747
SPECIAL OPERATIONS UNIT

788
00:51:14,383 --> 00:51:16,803
We'll take over from here. Stay inside.

789
00:51:16,886 --> 00:51:19,097
[tense music playing]

790
00:51:49,877 --> 00:51:50,753
[sighs]

791
00:52:20,867 --> 00:52:21,701
Clear.

792
00:52:23,452 --> 00:52:24,287
Clear.

793
00:52:25,246 --> 00:52:26,080
All clear.

794
00:52:26,164 --> 00:52:27,206
[music fades]

795
00:52:27,748 --> 00:52:28,833
[sighs]

796
00:53:01,699 --> 00:53:03,409
Get out!

797
00:53:08,372 --> 00:53:09,665
[cell phone buzzes]

798
00:53:17,340 --> 00:53:20,426
[car alarms blaring in distance]

799
00:53:22,303 --> 00:53:23,554
[dramatic music playing]

800
00:53:23,638 --> 00:53:25,723
[indistinct chatter]

801
00:53:29,810 --> 00:53:34,565
[Gun-woo gasping]

802
00:53:34,649 --> 00:53:35,983
Somebody help!

803
00:53:37,610 --> 00:53:40,571
NO CALLER ID

804
00:53:40,655 --> 00:53:42,865
[somber music playing]

805
00:53:42,949 --> 00:53:44,450
This is your fault.

806
00:53:45,368 --> 00:53:46,202
How's that feel?

807
00:53:46,285 --> 00:53:48,287
-[indistinct chatter]
-[breathes deeply]

808
00:53:48,371 --> 00:53:50,081
I told you this would happen.

809
00:53:50,831 --> 00:53:54,543
I said if only you'd fight me
just one time… Just once, you asshole!

810
00:53:58,547 --> 00:53:59,715
But you don't listen.

811
00:54:00,967 --> 00:54:02,760
Your coach's hand will be next.

812
00:54:03,261 --> 00:54:04,387
What do you say?

813
00:54:05,805 --> 00:54:06,764
[exhales]

814
00:54:06,847 --> 00:54:08,683
Huh? What do you say?

815
00:54:08,766 --> 00:54:10,768
[suspenseful music playing]

816
00:54:13,312 --> 00:54:14,480
Where do I meet you?

817
00:54:15,648 --> 00:54:18,526
That's right. That's the right attitude.

818
00:54:19,443 --> 00:54:20,861
Wait for my next call.

819
00:54:30,329 --> 00:54:32,665
[music swells]

820
00:54:32,748 --> 00:54:34,417
[music fades]

821
00:54:34,500 --> 00:54:36,502
[dramatic music playing]

822
00:55:01,944 --> 00:55:03,946
[music fades]

823
00:55:04,905 --> 00:55:06,907
[suspenseful music playing]

824
00:57:32,094 --> 00:57:33,053
[music stops]
